@NODE Introduction

@{b}Introduction:@{ub}
-------------
        
Have you tried playing computer backgammon before?  Were you a little
disappointed?

In the long run, most users will find that this program plays a very
competitive game of backgammon.  Anyone from beginner to expert will 
improve their game by playing and using ProGammon.

This program keeps track of your wins and losses as well as gammons and
backgammons.  The Statistics Page also tabulates each dice roll so you 
can examine the dice for randomness and fairness.

ProGammon works in most any screen mode, it's operating system friendly
yet remains small and very efficient.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements

@{b}Requirements:@{ub}
-------------
       
The screen mode requester that ProGammon uses requires version 38 
of the asl.library which was included with Amiga OS 2.1.

Kickstart 2.04 users can use either the WORKBENCH tool type or the
SCREEN tool type to select their preferred screen mode.

The latest version of this program was developed on a PC using 
@{" WinUAE " LINK WinUAE}.

